               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary"> The Dīvān of poet <persName>Ḥaydar Haravī (d.
                        1552)</persName>, popularly known as <addName
                        ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/24162178770507850614"
                        key="person_24162178770507850614">Kulūch</addName> (Biscuit) or <addName
                        ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/24162178770507850614"
                        key="person_24162178770507850614">Kulūchah-Paz</addName> on account of his
                     profession as a biscuit-baker and merchant. Originally from Herat, his trade
                     took him to India. Despite the poet's contemporary, Timurid vizier
                        <persName>Mīr ‘Alī Shīr Navā'ī</persName> description of him in the
                        <title>Majālis al-Nafā'is</title> (Assemblies of Elegancies) as illiterate
                     and of modest talent, an opinion repatedly cited by subsequent authors, his
                     works have only very recently received critical scholarly attention.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_281-item1">
                     <author ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/24162178770507850614"
                        key="person_24162178770507850614">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Ḥaydar Haravī, d. 1552</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">دیوان حیدر هروی</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Ḥaydar Kulūchah-paz</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">حیدر کلوچه پز</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Ḥaydar Kulūchah</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">حیدر کلوچه</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20389" change="#ids-cleanup">Dīvān-i
                        Ḥaydar Haravī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_20389" change="#ids-cleanup">دیوان حیدر
                        هروی</title>
                     <title type="alt" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20389"
                        change="#ids-cleanup">Dīvān-i Ḥaydar Kulūchah-paz</title>
                     <title type="alt" xml:lang="fa" key="work_20389" change="#ids-cleanup">دیوان
                        حیدر کلوچه پز</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa"><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ (folio 1b):</locus> بیا
                        رب یا ربم تا روز بی ماه رخت شبها.</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa"><locus from="89b" to="89b"> برگ ۸۹پ (folio
                           89b):</locus> تمت الکتاب بعون الله وحسن توفیقه</explicit>
                     <colophon>No colophon.</colophon>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note><persName>Ḥamīd Riz̤ā Ṭahmāsbī</persName> recently-published a critical
                        edition of this Divan.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
